Case No. 15,761. UNITED STATES v. MEYER. Circuit Court, D. Pennsylvania. Oct., 1799. Federal Jurisdiction—Common Law Offences.

[This was an indictment for libel, and is cited in Wharton's Precedents of Indictments, § 903. note, as an instance of the exercise by the federal courts of jurisdiction over offences, of a purely common law origin. The case is no-were reported; opinion not now accessible.]
